title: Cornhusker Marching Band, reel 3
description: Digitized video (without audio) of the University of Nebraska-Lincoln Marching Band in the 1949-1950 academic year. The video content includes the following topics: University of Missouri Band; Nebraska Band, Evolution of the Dance; Minuet, Indian Dance, Square dance, Charleston, jitterbug; Faculty salute; Hypo needle, dollar sign, T-square & triangle, lamp of learning; Scale of Justice, RX (pharmacy).
subject: Military, Band, R.O.T.C. Cadet; Marching Band (Musical group); Cornhusker Marching Band
isPartOf/Collection: Donald A. Lentz, Marching Band Records
rights: For copyright information, please contact the repository.
publisher: Archives & Special Collections, University of Nebraska-Lincoln Libraries

title: Cornhusker Marching Band, reel 4
description: Digitized video (without audio) of the University of Nebraska-Lincoln Marching Band in 1943, 1947, 1952, and 1954. The video content includes the following precision drills: long columns (1947); short columns shot at slower speed (1952); and drills at Missouri used in the Orange Bowl (1954).
subject: Military, Band, R.O.T.C. Cadet; Marching Band (Musical group); Cornhusker Marching Band
isPartOf/Collection: Donald A. Lentz, Marching Band Records
rights: For copyright information, please contact the repository.
publisher: Archives & Special Collections, University of Nebraska-Lincoln Libraries

title: Cornhusker Marching Band, reel 5
description: Digitized video (without audio) of the University of Nebraska-Lincoln Marching Band in 1954. The video content includes the following drills: Band Day "100"; Halloween drills (pumpkin, ghost, cat, and bat); University of Colorado Buffalo and Precision drills (pin-wheels, hexagon, files, and diamonds); drills for 12 months at the University of Pittsburgh Homecoming game (bell, heart, shamrock, umbrella, flower, bridal, firecracker, fish, R-R-R school, pumpkin, turkey, and Christmas tree).
